| Networking Device                  | Main Function                                                                                                                                 | Real-Life Example                                                                                                            |
| ---------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
|   Modem                            | Connects your home or office network to the Internet Service Provider (ISP) by converting the ISP's signal into a usable internet connection. | Home or office: Connected to the ISP's fiber, cable, or DSL line to provide internet access.                                 |
|   Router                           | Shares the internet connection between multiple devices, assigns IP addresses, and manages network traffic (wired and Wi-Fi).                 | Home: Used to connect laptops, smartphones, smart TVs, and other devices to the internet.                                    |
|   Switch                           | Connects multiple wired devices within the same local network and transfers data efficiently between them.                                    | Office or computer lab: Connects desktop computers, printers, and servers using Ethernet cables.                             |
|   Access Point (AP)                | Provides or extends Wi-Fi coverage by allowing wireless devices to connect to the network.                                                    | School, hotel, or large home: Extends Wi-Fi to areas where the main router's signal is weak.                                 |
|   Network Cable (Ethernet Cable)   | Physically connects network devices and carries data between them at high speed.                                                              | Desktop computer to router/switch: Provides a fast and stable wired internet connection for gaming, work, or file transfers. |
